column14: What is your annual household income?
column15: What was your overall impression of this event (quality, lighting, sound, value)?
column16: Please share any other suggestions or ideas that would help us enhance your experience at Gesa Power House Theatre. If you would like someone to respond to your feedback, please include your contact information. Thank you!

column15: Such a wonderful event. Such a moving night with amazing stories.

It was good, a hard subject to hear about at times (Red Badge Proect) but important.  The sound was excellent, even the quieter voices could easily be heard in the back.  The program was quite long, maybe one less speaker in the first half and one less in the second?  Or two less overall with no intermission?
column16: It is a great place, and we are lucky to have it in town.  Thank you!

column15: Excellent venue for this event - light and sound was wonderful.  I could see and hear everything.  The event was well organized, moved along without a hitch, and each of the speakers was prepared   All those details are very much appreciated.  The event itself was so powerful - the speakers, the stories, the writing, the vulnerability.  I felt really privileged to be told the stories.
column16: Thank you for a wonderful event.

column15: Value is excellent, lighting was good, looked and felt clean, lecturn/podium was wobbly each time a reader went up and placed their hands on it
column16: Fix, or even better, get a new lecturn. The finish is coming off of the side where people put their hands.

column15: Very worthwhile event. But turn the lights down. I had to put my cap on to shield my eyes from the overwhelming lights.
So sorry, we had the dates wrong and did not attend. So disappointed to have missed this.
Excellent venue. There was a background sound during a couple of the Veteran’s telling their stories. Someone finally got it turned off.
column16: Many thanks for allowing this wonderful organization of veterans to tell their incredible stories. It was much appreciated!

column15: great  I have been to many shows there. All have been good.
The venue is nice. There was a squeaking fan that was distracting from the speakers.

Very excellent though the speakers commented a bit on the lights being too bright. From the sound and fullness of the audience I was very pleased.  Most importantly, this event was a real encouragement to anyone with pride in our nation and care about our military service men and women. I will attend Red Badge again in the future and tell my veteran friends about it.
Powerful, moving, thought-provoking, worth every minute of my time to attend.  The setting is intimate and perfect.

Lighting seemed harsh.  Otherwise okay.
I really enjoyed listening to the Veterans telling (reading) their personal stories.  What good therapy for them…and good for the audience hearing them!
it all seemed fine to me.

My husband and I had a great experience. The emcee was fantastic and the readings were quality in terms of writing, presenting, and - most importantly - allowing us to see a bit of their story and/or their inner world. It was a moving experience, well worth the time, and we plan to attend again in the future. A flier with more information about Red Badge might be a good addition next time.
